Author: not_quite_aesthetic
Text: I feel like the ED recovery community tends to be pretty judgmental when someone starts to "go beyond" their recovery to focus on other goals-- when in reality I think that's a pretty natural part of recovery itself. Her mindset seems to be similar to your average person who just got into fitness. She has goals around her body, but they don't seem unhealthy, and she seems a lot more lax around food than she used to be. She's not my favorite recovery youtuber by any means, but I think the comments were overly harsh
